-- Fort Larned, I’ll Have Another, Wise Dan Vie for Horse of Year
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-01-06T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-06/fort-larned-i-ll-have-another-wise-dan-vie-for-horse-of-year.html
Breeders’ Cup Classic winner Fort
Larned, Kentucky Derby and  Preakness Stakes  champion I’ll Have
Another and Breeders’ Cup Mile winner Wise Dan are finalists for
2012 Horse of the Year honors.  Winners in the 17 horse and human categories will be
announced at the 42nd annual Eclipse Awards on Jan. 19 at
Gulfstream Park in Hallandale Beach, Florida.  Havre de Grace became the third consecutive filly to win
the award in 2011, following Zenyatta in 2010 and  Rachel
Alexandra  in 2009.  I’ll Have Another also is vying for top 3-year-old male
against Bodemeister and Union Rags, while Fort Larnet and Wise
Dan are competing against Little Mike for Older Male champion.  Todd Pletcher ,  Bob Baffert  and Dale Romans are finalists
for trainer of the year and Javier Castellano, Ramon Dominguez
and  John Velazquez  were nominated for top jockey.  Reddam Racing LLC, Midwest Thoroughbreds Inc. and
Goldolphin Racing LLC are competing as best owner.  The finalists were nominated by 254 members of the National
Thoroughbred Racing Association, Daily Racing Form and the
National Turf Writers and Broadcasters.  The Eclipse Awards were named after the 18th-century
racehorse Eclipse, who began racing at age five and was
undefeated in 18 starts. They are given to horses and
individuals whose outstanding achievements in North America have
earned them the title of Champion in their respective
categories.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
